 all that state management…

00:31:20.440 --> 00:31:21.440
 Yeah.

00:31:21.440 --> 00:31:22.440
 Yeah.

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:23.440
 …and transmission?

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:24.840
 But even if we can…

00:31:24.840 --> 00:31:28.000
 If the Tachyon team can solve all that, we can get it deployed, get all the wallets or

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:35.440
 some wallets to support it, that extra bandwidth can be used for post-quantum signatures and

00:31:35.440 --> 00:31:42.320
 encryption, but that doesn't protect against a quantum computer counterfeiting Zcash, which

00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:47.520
 is almost like the… would be… if you could just pick one thing to protect… to prevent

00:31:47.520 --> 00:31:49.120
 quantum computers for doing…

00:31:49.120 --> 00:31:50.120
 Yeah.

00:31:50.120 --> 00:31:51.120
 Yeah.

00:31:51.120 --> 00:31:52.120
 …preventing them from counterfeiting Zcash would be a great pick.

00:31:52.120 --> 00:31:53.120
 Yeah.

00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:54.120
 Yeah.

00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:55.120
 I agree.

00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:56.120
 I agree.

00:31:56.120 --> 00:31:57.120
 It's the thing they would probably want to do most if…

00:31:57.120 --> 00:31:58.120
 Yes.

00:31:58.120 --> 00:31:59.120
 …if they could do stuff to you.

00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:00.120
 Yeah.

00:32:00.120 --> 00:32:01.120
 Yeah.

00:32:01.120 --> 00:32:04.280
 And it makes sense the way the Tachyon team and the Valar team, of what little I understand

00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:08.820
 of how they've been sketching out this roadmap, is to sort of do the things that we know how

00:32:08.820 --> 00:32:13.820
 to do now, that we could do sooner, and the things that protect privacy against future

00:32:13.820 --> 00:32:18.280
 quantum attackers, because if they want to violate your privacy, they can look back in

00:32:18.280 --> 00:32:19.280
 time to violate your privacy.

