 I was going to say it's now inaccessible.

00:35:54.560 --> 00:35:55.560
 Oh, okay.

00:35:55.560 --> 00:35:56.560
 Right?

00:35:56.560 --> 00:35:57.560
 Like, you can't…

00:35:57.560 --> 00:35:58.560
 Let's just say, whatever, like…

00:35:58.560 --> 00:35:59.560
 Yeah, hypothetically.

00:35:59.560 --> 00:36:04.100
 The easy way to do it is just make T-addresses invalid in the blockchain, which effectively

00:36:04.100 --> 00:36:07.600
 means burning everyone's money that's currently in T-addresses.

00:36:07.600 --> 00:36:12.040
 There's no way to, like, force-shield it all.

00:36:12.040 --> 00:36:16.440
 So let's just say, for the sake – the point of this story is, the devs cannot…

00:36:16.440 --> 00:36:19.360
 Take away a feature from the users, right?

00:36:19.360 --> 00:36:24.060
 So if we did all that, we went through that process, we uploaded all that software, any

00:36:24.060 --> 00:36:27.700
 users who still wanted to keep their money that was currently in a T-address, or they

00:36:27.700 --> 00:36:31.700
 still wanted to be able to send and receive with T-addresses, they just wouldn't install

00:36:31.700 --> 00:36:35.260
 that software, they'd keep using the software they currently have, which currently works

00:36:35.260 --> 00:36:36.260
 for them.

00:36:36.260 --> 00:36:41.440
 Like, I do think there's, like, a very important aspect of T-addresses for, like,

00:36:41.440 --> 00:36:46.320
 institutions, for exchanges, where, for example, as we were speaking of…

00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:52.140
 Earlier, you wouldn't necessarily want an entity like Cypherpunk, for example, to have

00:36:52.140 --> 00:36:57.520
 their coins shielded, because that would prevent transparency.

00:36:57.520 --> 00:37:02.080
 So users would not be able to audit that Cypherpunk does indeed hold these tokens.

00:37:02.080 --> 00:37:04.820
 Yeah, transparency is good for some purposes.

00:37:04.820 --> 00:37:06.820
 Yes.

00:37:06.820 --> 00:37:10.700
 And that optional, you know, and especially for exchanges who want to, you know, stay

00:37:10.700 --> 00:37:14.200
 within the law, they may be forced to, you know…

00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:15.200
 Well, also…

00:37:15.200 --> 00:37:16.200
 The law…

00:37:16.200 --> 00:37:28.400
 Well, also, if they're custodying someone else's funds, funds owned by someone else,

00:37:28.400 --> 00:37:32.140
 I mean, I would rather they did that transparently, so we can all watch what they're doing.

00:37:32.140 --> 00:37:35.040
 You could have a view key on the other end.

00:37:35.040 --> 00:37:36.180
 That would be less…

00:37:36.180 --> 00:37:39.100
 That would be sort of a mixture…

00:37:39.100 --> 00:37:40.100
 How would that be better?

00:37:40.100 --> 00:37:46.080
 I mean, I guess you could then say, "Oh, we're fully shielded," but if you want to

00:37:46.080 --> 00:37:47.080
 have transparency, you can use a view key.

00:37:47.080 --> 00:37:48.080
 It's kind of like the same thing, but…

00:37:48.080 --> 00:37:49.080
 It's the same thing.

00:37:49.080 --> 00:37:50.080
 It's just more steps.

00:37:50.080 --> 00:37:51.080
 It's transparency with more steps.

00:37:51.080 --> 00:37:52.080
 Yeah.

00:37:52.080 --> 00:37:57.080
 And more steps is bad, because that makes it harder for the users.

00:37:57.080 --> 00:38:01.080
 It makes it easier for people to get confused or to get scammed or tricked.

00:38:01.080 --> 00:38:07.400
 So, anyway, I agree with you, or I agree with what you were saying, that transparency has

00:38:07.400 --> 00:38:08.400
 its uses.

00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:09.400
 Yeah.

00:38:09.400 --> 00:38:14.080
 And also, just in general, like, if the users…

00:38:14.080 --> 00:38:15.080
 I really like a certain kind of humility.

00:38:15.080 --> 00:38:16.080
 Yeah.

00:38:16.080 --> 00:38:23.080
 Like, if I think 80% of the people out there should behave differently than they do…

00:38:23.080 --> 00:38:24.080
 Yeah.

00:38:24.080 --> 00:38:26.580
 It's like, "I'm not wrong.

00:38:26.580 --> 00:38:27.580
 The children are wrong."

00:38:27.580 --> 00:38:28.580
 Right?

