 Like, when the price is going up, everyone says, "Don't change anything and ruin it."

00:39:24.960 --> 00:39:25.960
 It's working.

00:39:25.960 --> 00:39:26.960
 Don't ruin it.

00:39:26.960 --> 00:39:27.960
 It's working.

00:39:27.960 --> 00:39:28.960
 Yeah.

00:39:28.960 --> 00:39:29.960
 Like, don't touch it.

00:39:29.960 --> 00:39:30.960
 And when the price is going down, everyone says, "Devs, do something."

00:39:30.960 --> 00:39:31.960
 Yes.

00:39:31.960 --> 00:39:38.600
 And also, a lot of the opposition to Crosslink and a lot of the other recent, like, governance

00:39:38.600 --> 00:39:44.840
 and strategic and mimetic debates within Zcash have been about comparing Zcash to Bitcoin.

00:39:44.840 --> 00:39:45.840
 Yeah.

00:39:45.840 --> 00:39:46.840
 Yeah.

00:39:46.840 --> 00:39:47.840
 And so, that whole movement was the Zcash equals encrypted Bitcoin movement.

00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:48.840
 Yeah.

00:39:48.840 --> 00:39:49.840
 Yeah.

00:39:49.840 --> 00:39:50.840
 Yeah.

